title: Bears roar in second half, shut out Creekside
text:
Bears roar in second half, shut out Creekside 
Sat, Oct 3, 2015 @ 12:04 am | updated Sat, Oct 3, 2015 @ 2:45 am 
BARTRAM TRAIL 31 
CREEKSIDE 0 
Bartram broke open a scoreless game in the third quarter with three successive big plays to lead the Bears (4-2, 2-0 in Region 3-7A) to a home victory over rival Creekside (0-6, 0-1). WR AJ Bolden hauled in a 45-yard pass from QB Jordan Smith, on a third-and-10 play, with 10:37 left in the third quarter for a 7-0 lead. Isaiah Bolden, AJâ€™s cousin, took a Creekside punt 77 yards for a TD just three minutes later to gain a 14-0 lead. ... Knights senior RB Blake Morgan rushed for 169 yards in the loss one year after Creekside beat Bartram for the only time in school history. ... Bartram QB Joey Gatewood was suspended for the game and did not play.
